  "title": "QUANTITY SURVEYOR",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Responsible for quantity take-off and cost estimation for quotation/tender and on-going projects with specific deadline.</li><li>Liaise with suppliers /Sub-contractors and source for competitive quotation.</li><li>Submission of monthly progress claim & variation order (VO).</li><li>Evaluation of sub-contractors’ progress claim & variation order.</li><li>Final account settlement with sub-contractors and clients.</li><li>Contract documents administration.</li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned by the management.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p><ul><li>At least 2 years of working experience with building construction</li><li>Preferred experience in full QS role in A1 Main-con.</li><li>Minimum Diploma in Civil Engineering / Building / Quantity Surveying or equivalent.</li><li>Proficient in MS Office.</li></ul>",
